other_tests.findings: The liver is diffusely echogenic consistent with fatty infiltration. No intra- or extra-hepatic biliary ductal dilatation; common bile duct measuring 4 mm. The main portal vein is patent with normal hepatopetal flow. The gallbladder is normal in appearance without intraluminal stones, and there is no pericholecystic fluid or wall thickening. Negative sonographic ___ sign. No right kidney hydronephrosis. No right upper quadrant ascites present.
